The question remains of what a good definition of ``almost discrete'' could be for a (not necessarily spatial) locale. One possibility is to mimic equation ${\mbox{\sf {\,int\,}}}{\mbox{\sf {\,cl\,}}}={\mbox{\sf {\,cl\,}}}$ by means of the notion of \emph{weak closure} for sublocales that, in its turn, depends on that of \emph{strong density} (see \cite{strong_density} and section \ref{section density} below). We shall note explore that possibility. Instead we shall investigate a class of locales, namely {\bf overlap algebras} (see section \ref{section o-algebras}), which correspond to topological spaces satisfying the following equation (see proposition \ref{spatial o-algebras}).


